title.children: Nathan Lyon limps from Lord's with potentially serious calf injruy

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A really poor pull shot from Pope, who backed away and just dabbed it to Steve Smith at deep backward square leg. It's not particularly clever batting from England, as another wicket does down almost of their own making. "There wasn't a slip, there wasn't a gully. Ollie Pope has just slogged that straight down Steve Smith's neck," Phil Tufnell says on ABC Radio. "I agree with Bazball, but you've got to have a brain as well. "Australia were dead and buried. They're all in the huddle congratulating themselves, that's annoyed me. It's all very well entertaining, but this is the Ashes. Now you've got to get the game back manageable again." He departs having made a start for 43.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: OUT! Ollie Pope is out!

children.content: A really poor pull shot from Pope, who backed away and just dabbed it to Steve Smith at deep backward square leg.
It's not particularly clever batting from England, as another wicket does down almost of their own making.
"There wasn't a slip, there wasn't a gully. Ollie Pope has just slogged that straight down Steve Smith's neck," Phil Tufnell says on ABC Radio.
"I agree with Bazball, but you've got to have a brain as well.

"Australia were dead and buried. They're all in the huddle congratulating themselves, that's annoyed me. It's all very well entertaining, but this is the Ashes. Now you've got to get the game back manageable again."
He departs having made a start for 43.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Michael Vaughan says on ABC Radio via the BBC that it looks like he's done his calf. "He is going to have to come off. The way he is walking doesn't look like cramp," he says. "Nathan Lyon did a world-class job at Edgbaston, he's only a few wickets away from reaching 500. "This is not a pretty sight for Australia."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Nathan Lyon helped off the field with a lower leg injury

children.content: Michael Vaughan says on ABC Radio via the BBC that it looks like he's done his calf.
"He is going to have to come off. The way he is walking doesn't look like cramp," he says.
"Nathan Lyon did a world-class job at Edgbaston, he's only a few wickets away from reaching 500.
"This is not a pretty sight for Australia."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well. Well. That was one hell of a session for England going at better than five runs an over and making this bowling attack look harmless. Mitchell Starc is looking particularly brutal on his recall, going at 7.8 an over in his seven. The pitch isn't doing anything, so we'll see if Australia can muster something in the final session after a cuppa.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: TEA: England 1-145 (Duckett 62, Pope 32)
